{"/service/ndnp/arhi/batch_arhi_lunar_ver01/data/sn90050268/00513688866/1921011001/0713.xml":{"full_text":"ITS TIME THE BUYING STRIKE IS OVER\nk\nWhat\u2019s the matter with the buying\npublic today. It is the plainest, simplest\nsolution in the world. Even the most cas\nual observer could tell you in a minute\nwhy people stooped short of buying\na few months ago. To begin with\nbig business got scared and the peo\nple found it out and naturally, they\nquit buying, thinking that things\nwould come down in a jump. Prices\ndid not go up all at once, neither will they\ncome down in a crash. Many people have\nbeen putting off buying the things that\nthey actually need with the thought par\namount in their minds that the bottom\nwould be reached shortly and then they\nwould supply their needs. These same\npeople who have had this thought no\ndoubt were dependent more or less on the\nconstant revolution of business activities\nto maintain them and their jobs. When\npeople stop buying and trading and do\ning business it createst a depression and\nwhen business depression is felt men\nloose jobs and can\u2019t buy what they need.\nEvery business is more or less de\npendent on the other the same as one\nman\u2019s success is largely responsible for\nsome other man\u2019s success.\nThis condition is practically passed\nnow\u2019 and people are looking out into the\nfuture with a more hopeful eye as to the\nreal conditions in America today.\nThere is at present a greater abund\nance of crops in the w\u2019orld than there has\nbeen for years. By the great strain that\nhas just passed the American banking in\nstitutions have proven that they are\nas strong as the rock of Gibraltar. The\ntransportation system of the country has\nbeen greatly relieved and commerce can\nbe carried on better now\u2019 than ever since\nthe war and the railroads are in a better\nfinancial condition than they have ever\nbeen. Despite the great wave of spending\nthat has been prevalent in this country\nduring the war and since, there is yet a\ngreat surplus of money today due no\ndoubt to the past five years of inflated\nprosperity.\n3 sirmemwv\u2014\nBusiness depression is a mere state of\nmind and undoubtedly this state has been\nreached and forgotten. The great major\nity of business men are more optimistic\nnow than they have been for months and\nwhy should those w\u2019ho have less appear so\npessimistic now.\nThe time to arise is now\u2019 and the time\nto busy yourself with your business is\nnow.\n*lf we w\u2019ill all w\u2019ork and do and save\nand buy, the country is safe, but on the\nother hand, if we all stop w\u2019ork and brood\nand stop buying and w\u2019ant, it will only be\na short time until we will again be in the\nmidst of a depression that is now grad\nually passing.\nTHE DAILY GUARD\nJared E. Trevathan, Manager.\nL PtTONE 26.\nIf Herbert Hoover Took\nHold of the Arkansas Cotton\nCondition Don\u2019t you Believe\nHe Would Soon Secure a\nt Better Price?\nI While there is no intimation that it is possible to set Mr.\nHoover to labor in such a field, yet Mr. Hooter is coming to the con\n/enece of\nI BANKERS MERCHANTS AND FARMERS j\nLITTLE ROCK. ARh_ JANUARY IHI9\n\nI\nMR. HOOVER\nWill no doubt give those in attendance his ideas on trade condi\ntions, and how they may be benefited. He has had rare opportun\nities to study conditions in general, and will probably suggest some\nmethod for combatting the existing low price on cotton, as well as\nstabilising the crop in the future.\nTHEODORE PRICE\nJs a cotton expert with an international reputation. He will talk\nI/rom a different angle, and his suggestions should be practical and\nbeneficial.\n\nThere will be many other speakers of wide experience, all dis\ncussing a different phase of the cotton industry. From their sug\ngestions a solution which will add millions to our crop values\nshould come.\nTHIS CONFERENCE WILL PAY HANDSOME RETURNS\nFROM THE BEGINNING, AS IT WILL INCREASE THE MOR\nALE OF THE BUSINESS WORLD, SO FAR AS ARKANSAS IS\n.CONCERNED. IT WILL CONVINCE THE MERCHANTS.\n1 .BANKERS AND FARMERS THAT CONDITIONS ARE RE-\n.MARKABLY GOOD FOR A RECONSTRUCTION PERIOD\nTHEY WILL CEASE CRYING HARD TIMES AND GET DOWN\nTO REAL WORK.\nI\nPreparation* are being made to entertain 5,000 merchants,\nbankers and farmers at this big conference. Make your hotel reser\nvation early. There will be no advance in hotel or restaurant rates\nYou will find their prices lower than in any other city the sixe of\nLittle Rock in rhe United States.\n1\nPull the Latch String\non January 18-19\n0 1\n\n|FRATERNAL ORDERS\nMT. ZION LODGE NO. It.\nF. A. M.\nI Meets First and Third Thur*dty\nNights in Each Month.\nNext Meeting\u2014\nThursday night, January 20.\nj BATES!ILLE H APTER. NO. 9.\nR. A. M.\n\u20221 Stated ton location*. LaM Tuesday\nNight in Each Month.\nNext Meeting\u2014\nTuesday night. January 25.\nt>T. ELMO (OMMANDERY NO. IX\nKNIGHTS TEMPI AR\nMeet* Second Friday Night in Each\nMonth.\nNext Meeting\u2014\nFriday n.ght, January 14.\nRI IH CHAPTER. NO. 91. <l. E. S.\ni Meet* Second and Fourth Thursday\nAfternoon* in Each Month at\nMasonic Hall.\nNext Meeting\u2014\nThursday afternoon, Januar* IS.\nI. O. O. F.\nMeets Every Friday Night in Each\nMeath.\nNext Meeting\u2014\nFriday night, January 14.\nWHEN WORKIVG\nFORCES ARE CUT\nIn times of business depression the\npoorest workers sre laid off first and\nI efficient men and women retained.\n1 1 backache, stiff muscles, aching joints,\nI hands and feet, rheumatic\npains and other symptoms of kidney\ntrouble keep many persons below par.\nFoley Kidney Pills help tired, weak\nkidneys.\nSold by Druggists everywhere.\nCITY OFFICERS\nJ. Paul Ward, Mayor.\nT. Albert, Recorder.\nChas. C. Houston, Marshal.\nG. E. Gathri.ht, Treasurer.\nM. <asev. City Attorney.\nM. S. Craig, City Health Officer\nT. M. Scarlett. Sextos\nUse it Thun Decide\nkJ- I\n4>\nWe Will Lend You\nA Val\u00abt AuloMmp Kaawr lore K> dog\ntrwl I ,haa da. dr i keep w. p